Visit for: This visit is for evaluation of a new patient.
Christine HENRICHS is a 76 year old female.
76 yowf with multiple medical diagnoses as documented.

Pt is being transferred to HCSP long term for higher level of care. Notes from ALF state one of the reasons is for improved care for incontinence. Pt is a pleasant, elderly female, oriented to self and place. She has a history of COPD due to extensive tobacco use hx, though she did stop about 20 years ago.

She has a history of heart disease which is vague and she describes as "stress heart disease". She apparently had a recent episode of chest pain which was evaluated in ER without acute findings and has a follow up appt with cardiology.
Pt is sitting in TV area today, pleasant, cooperative, without complaint.

Pt with altered gait requiring rollator, at risk for falls with injuries. Continue to enforce safety protocols.
Continue to monitor urinary symptoms with U/A pending at this time.
